1 parent's child under the Individuals with Disabilities Education Act [Pub . L .
2 108 - 446; 20 U.S.C. 1412(a)(10)(A)]; and
3 f. To notify the departmen t if the parent's student terminates participation in the
4 education savings account program and enrolls in a public school .
5 5. A parent participating in the education savings account program shall use the funds
6 deposited in the eligible student's account for the following qualifying expenses to
7 educate the eligible studen t :
8 a. Tuition and fees at a participating school;
9 b. A textbook required by a participating school;
10 c. Payment for private tutoring or to another educational service provider;
11 d. Payment for purchase of curriculum;
12 e. Tuition or fees for a nonpublic online learning program;
13 f. Fees for national norm-referenced examinations, advanced placement
14 examinations or similar courses, and any examinations related to college or
15 university admission;
16 g. Computer hardware, software, or other technological device that is used solely
17 for a student's educational needs and approved by the department or a licensed
18 physician, provided hardware purchased with education savings account funds
19 may not be resold within one year of purchase;
20 h. Reasonable fees for transportation paid to a fee - for - service transportation
21 provider for the student to travel to and from an education service provider;
22 i. Tuition and fees at an eligible postsecondary institution;
23 j. A textbook required for college or university courses.
24 6. A participating school, private tutor, eligible postsecondary institution, or other
25 education service provider may not refund, rebate, or share a student's grant with a
26 parent or the student in any manner.
27 7. A parent may make a payment for the cost of educational programs and services not
28 covered by the funds in the child's account.
29 8. The state treasurer annually shall transfer the funds required for education savings
30 accounts from the general fund to the Bank of North Dakota for quarterly deposit in
31 each education savings account.
