20 (a) Satisfaction with the education savings account program ; and
21 (b) Opinions on other topics, items, or issues that may indicate the
22 effectiveness of the education savings account program.
23 4. A participating nonpublic school or other education service provider is autonomous
24 and not an agent of the state or federal government and:
25 a. The departmen t may not regulate the educational program of a participating
26 nonpublic school or education service provider that accepts funds from an
27 education savings account, except as provided under this chapter and chapter
28 15.1 - 23 ;
29 b. The creation of the education savings account program does not expand the
30 regulatory authority of the state, its officers, or a school district to impose an
31 additional regulation of nonpublic schools or education service providers beyond
